# BigCommerce (Catalyst) Standards

## GraphQL Storefront API

- All GraphQL operations use `gql.tada` `graphql()` from `core/client/graphql.ts`. Do not call raw `fetch` against the GraphQL endpoint.
- Reuse fragments from `core/client/fragments/` (`PricingFragment`, etc.).
- Honour fragment masking: consume `FragmentOf<T>` via `readFragment(Fragment, masked)`.
- Pass `currencyCode` and pagination cursors (`first`/`after`) explicitly.
- Selection sets must be lean — every requested field consumed by the UI.

## REST Management API (server-only)

- Base URL: `https://api.bigcommerce.com/stores/${BIGCOMMERCE_STORE_HASH}/v3/...` (some endpoints use `/v2/`).
- Auth: `X-Auth-Token: ${BIGCOMMERCE_ACCESS_TOKEN}`. Never expose in client bundles or `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
- Lives only in route handlers or server actions. `runtime = 'nodejs'`.
- `cache: 'no-store'` for any PII (customers, orders).
- Honour rate limits — read `X-Rate-Limit-Requests-Left`, back off on 429.

## Channel scoping

- Every Storefront API request is channel-scoped via `BIGCOMMERCE_CHANNEL_ID`.
- For multi-storefront, resolve channel per request via `beforeRequest` and scope cart cookies per channel.
- Never share a `cartId` cookie across channels.

## Secrets

Browser-safe values (only with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix and after careful review):
- (none in default Catalyst setup — keep everything server-side)

Server-only values (NEVER exposed):
- `BIGCOMMERCE_ACCESS_TOKEN` (REST Management)
- `BIGCOMMERCE_STOREFRONT_TOKEN` (Storefront JWT; treat as server-only by default)
- Customer impersonation token (minted server-side, attached to `client.fetch`)
- `AUTH_SECRET` (Auth.js)
- `B2B_API_TOKEN`
- `MAKESWIFT_SITE_API_KEY`
- `BIGCOMMERCE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`
- `BIGCOMMERCE_CLIENT_SECRET`

## Caching

| Query type | Strategy |
| --- | --- |
| Anonymous catalog read | `next: { revalidate: <target>, tags: [TAGS.xxx] }` |
| Customer-scoped read (cart, customer, orders) | `cache: 'no-store'` |
| Mutation | `cache: 'no-store'` then `revalidateTag(TAGS.xxx)` |

- Tag every cached query. Untagged caches cannot be invalidated by webhooks.
- Never `force-cache` on customer-scoped queries — privacy hazard.
- Customer impersonation token must always be paired with `cache: 'no-store'`.

## RSC vs client

- Default to React Server Components. `'use client'` only when interactivity demands it.
- Never call GraphQL Storefront or REST Management from a client component — all data lives in RSC or server actions.
- Pass only serialisable props from RSC to client.

## Server actions

- File pattern: `app/.../_actions/<verb>.ts` with `'use server'` at the top.
- Validate `FormData` with Zod (Conform's `parseWithZod`).
- After mutations, `revalidateTag(TAGS.cart)` (or relevant tag).
- Mask BC error messages before returning to the client.

## Webhooks

- Path: `app/api/webhooks/.../route.ts`.
- `export const runtime = 'nodejs'`. `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`.
- Verify signature with `crypto.timingSafeEqual` against `BIGCOMMERCE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`.
- Idempotency on `payload.hash` (Redis/DB, 24h TTL).
- Respond 2xx within 5s. Push heavy work to a queue.
- Invalidate the cache tags that match the event scope.

## Makeswift

- Register components with `runtime.registerComponent` in a side-effect file under `core/lib/makeswift/components/`.
- Side-effect imports added to a central register (often `core/lib/makeswift/register-components.ts`).
- `MAKESWIFT_SITE_API_KEY` is server-only.
- Use `siteVersion: 'Working'` in draft mode (`draftMode().isEnabled === true`), otherwise `'Live'`.
- Makeswift catch-all route should resolve last — let real Catalyst routes (PDP, PLP) match first.

## Customer auth

- Default: Auth.js v5 (beta) + BC Customer Login API. Session token stored in HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax cookie.
- Customer impersonation token retrieved via `getSessionCustomerAccessToken()` in server code.
- JWT SSO redirect: sign with `BIGCOMMERCE_CLIENT_SECRET`, `expiresIn: '30s'`, include `store_hash`, `channel_id`. Verify identity before signing.
- reCAPTCHA on registration and password reset.

## B2B Edition

- Check `B2B_EDITION_ENABLED` server-side before importing B2B client or rendering B2B-only UI.
- Mint B2B session token per-customer via `/api/io/auth/storefront`; cache by customer ID with short TTL.
- Sales rep impersonation: persistent "Shopping as ..." banner; audit every action with rep ID + buyer ID.
- Enforce spend limits and role gating server-side.

## Testing

- Vitest + React Testing Library + MSW for unit/integration.
- MSW intercepts GraphQL by operation name (`graphql.query('Name', ...)`).
- Mock Next.js helpers with `vi.mock('next/headers', ...)` and `vi.mock('next/cache', ...)`.
- RSC cannot render in jsdom — extract data-shaping logic into pure functions or rely on Playwright for full rendering.
- Playwright runs against a dedicated test channel; never against production.
